# Vue 3 + TypeScript Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Vue 3 with Composition API and script setup
- TypeScript strict mode
- Pinia for state management
- Vue Router 4
- Vite

## Component Rules
- Always use `<script setup lang="ts">` — no Options API
- Multi-word component names required (`UserCard`, not `Card`)
- Props: define with `defineProps<{ ... }>()`
- Emits: define with `defineEmits<{ ... }>()`
- Expose: use `defineExpose()` only for parent refs

## Composables
- One concern per composable
- Prefix: `use` + PascalCase (`useUserProfile.ts`)
- Return reactive refs/computed, not raw values

## Pinia Stores
- One store per domain
- Actions for async operations
- Getters for derived state
- No direct state mutation outside actions

## Template Rules
- `v-if` takes priority over `v-for` (never on same element)
- Use `:key` on all `v-for` — must be unique and stable
- Prefer `v-show` for frequent toggles, `v-if` for rarely shown elements
